 via the gsm system q how do you charge for the handset exchange service a in addition to standard cellular connection charges usminute minimum  minute domestic and international longdistance charges will accrue based on distance plus us taxes and a  service charge from cht q what is the japan handset exchange service a for cht customers traveling to japan cht has established a special partnership with japan’s largest mobile operator using the same phone number you can exchange your handset for a pdc handset from cht and enjoy international roaming from nearly everywhere in japan  of the country q prepaid cards a  ideal cardcomes with a mobile phone number face value nt includes nt connection credit valid for  days can be recharged and validity period extended using an additional id number refill cardhas a digit number printed on the card face values of nt nt and nt valid for  days used to recharge ideal card and extend its validity period without having to change numbers q what is international roaming service a international roaming is a service whereby mobile phone customers can use their cht mobile phone when traveling overseas international roaming can be divided into automatic roaming and nonautomatic roaming customers who apply for automatic international roaming can connect from overseas using their own mobile phone and their own phone number nonautomatic roaming means that you have to either change to a new number or switch to another handset to connect from abroad q can foreigners in taiwan apply for mobile phones a foreigners in taiwan need to have either an alien residence certificate arc or proof of employment from a domestic company to apply for a mobile phone foreigners in taiwan for a shortterm stay may not apply for a mobile phone q what is mobile short messaging service a short messaging service is used to transmit and receive short text messages using cht’s digital cellular network q how do i make or receive calls from abroad using international roaming a to make calls use the local calling method to receive calls if using your original mobile phone callers from taiwan simply call the same number they would call if you were in taiwan if using a different number callers in taiwan must dial the international access code  country code  the new roaming number to reach you q what happens if i lose my phone when using international roaming handset exchange services in the us or japan a please call the cht international roaming hotline to cancel your account because us and japanese authorities will have been notified that your account has been cancelled you will not be able to have your phone service reactivated after it has been cancelled q what is mobile party line a gsm mobile phone users can automatically connect with multiple parties at once this service requires no application and no additional charges are added q what is mobile call waiting a when customer a and customer b are talking customer a can still receive incoming calls from a third party customer a can then choose to talk to customer c or customer b this service is free of monthly service charges q what is mobile call forwarding a mobile customers with numbers beginning with  and  can set up a number for unanswered calls rings for more than  seconds to be forwarded to another cell phone or home phone number this service is free of monthly charges q what is mobile voice mail a when the phone is busy unanswered or the phone is turned off voice mail service can forward incoming calls to a voice mailbox system so that you do not miss important calls q how can i use my cellular phone in north america a chunghwa telecom provides two service solutions for roaming in north america handset exchange all cht mobile customers are eligible to trade their handset for an amps system phone allowing roaming in over  cities across north america gsm automatic roaming all cht mobile customers who have a triband or gsm mobile phone can automatically use their phone in o